nourish /ˈnʌrɪʃ/

(nourishing,nourished,nourishes) 

1. V-T To nourish a person, animal, or plant means to provide them with the food that is necessary for life, growth, and good health. 为…提供营养 

例： The food she eats nourishes both her and the baby. 她吃的食物为她和婴儿提供营养。 

2. nourishing ADJ 有营养的 

例： Most of these nourishing substances are in the yolk of the egg. 这些营养物质大部分在蛋黄里。

